    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>COVER-UP HURTS MITSUBISHI STOCK</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Miki Tanikawa</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Tanikawa, Miki</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Shares of Mitsubishi Motors fall 2 percent after company acknowledges that it had systematically covered up customer complaints since 1977 and would widen recall; graph (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The shares of Mitsubishi Motors fell a day after the company acknowledged that it had systematically covered up customer complaints since 1977 and would widen a recall. Its shares fell 2 percent on Tuesday. Still, analysts said that while the company's image might have been tarnished by the scandal, it would have no immediate effect on its earnings.</p>
        <p>Miki Tanikawa</p>
      </block>
